    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today with a focus on maximizing offensive upside against favorable pitching matchups. The anchor of our lineup is **Mickey Moniak**, who leads all starters with a massive 73.71 score. His date with Grant Holmes\u2014coupled with significant park factors and a dynamic platoon advantage\u2014makes him a mandatory start. He is closely followed by **Austin Riley**, who benefits from a high-ceiling 5.47 xERA matchup against Jose Quintana and a +19% boost from the opposing pitcher\u2019s skill profile. Additionally, **Brice Turang** (72.12) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.61) provide the elite sprint speed necessary to chase those scarce stolen bases, with **Brice Turang** specifically benefiting from a favorable order slot and a solid matchup against J. Irvin.\n\nWhile **Travis Bazzana** (49.02) was the most difficult exclusion from today\u2019s lineup, the optimizer ultimately favored the higher-floor projections of **Kyle Karros** and **Tyler Soderstrom**. **Travis Bazzana** boasts an elite .408 xwOBA, but his projected spot at the bottom of the order and the efficiency metrics of our middle-tier starters relegated him to the bench. We are keeping a close watch on **Josh Naylor**, who sits on the bench with a 43.14 score; he is essentially a \"break glass in case of emergency\" option, held out primarily due to a difficult matchup against the formidable Cole Ragans, whose 3.07 xERA poses a significant threat to our daily AVG floor. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given the high number of \"Lineup Pending\" designations across the board. We are particularly concerned with the volatility of **Dalton Rushing** (47.73), whose score suffers due to a suboptimal L/L platoon matchup against Matthew Liberatore. Furthermore, while **Gabriel Moreno** and **Seiya Suzuki** are currently projected to start, the \"Wind In\" advisory at their respective venues introduces a slight depressant on their power projections, which we have factored into their 57.75 and 59.22 scores. All managers should monitor the official lineup cards for **Dalton Rushing**, **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Brice Turang**, **Jose Caballero**, **Kyle Karros**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, **Mickey Moniak**, and **Austin Riley** to ensure the projected order holds.",
